==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Necrophore
<hw>Nec"ro*phore</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>nekro`s</grk> a dead body + <grk>fe`rein</grk> to bear.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any one of numerous species of beetles of the
genus <gen>Necrophorus</gen> and allied genera; -- called also
<altname>burying beetle</altname>, <altname>carrion beetle</altname>,
<altname>sexton beetle</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Necropolis</ent>⟦br⟧
